<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotherald.com/more/44.php" target="top">Patch 1.38</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Combat Style Notes: <br>
<br>
The bonus damage from a combat style now increases as the skill specialization of the style increases. Before, players would slowly &quot;outgrow&quot; lower level styles as the damage of their base attack increased thus rendering older styles effectively useless. In addition, styles that have openings or are at the end of three style &quot;chains&quot; do additional bonus damage with specialization since they are more difficult to use and happen more rarely.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotherald.com/more/48.php" target="top">Combat Style System Note</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
This change means that the more you train in a weapon specialization, the more damage styles you get from that specialization will do. <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">The only exception to this is the first style in each weapon specialization, which never grows in power.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> What this does for your character is that now you have many more styles available to you that in the previous version were &quot;too weak&quot; to use. You probably want to go back through all your older low-level styles (except the first one in each spec) and check it out again.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->_____________________________<br>
